
1. Install RVM (command from http://beginrescueend.com/rvm/install/)
$ bash < <(curl -s https://raw.github.com/wayneeseguin/rvm/master/binscripts/rvm-installer )

2. Install packages dependencies

2.1. System deps
$ sudo apt-get install po4a iso-codes tango-icon-theme

2.2. Compilation deps
$ sudo apt-get install libmagickcore-dev libpq-dev libreadline-dev

3. Open a new terminal (so that RVM path is loaded) and compile ruby
$ rvm install 1.8.7
$ rvm use 1.8.7
$ rvm gemset create dev
$ rvm 1.8.7@dev
$ gem update --system 1.4.1

You might want to change dev to something else or
create other gemsets.
Documentation on gemsets at http://beginrescueend.com/gemsets/basics/

4. Install bundler let bundler do the rest
$ gem install bundler
$ bundle install

